<subSubSection id="AC03DED79C85E5B45A3C627B3B9CF560" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E914FD524BB34E4AE674DAAAA634D294" pageId="18" pageNumber="131">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5BF2B42C48E387236DF3BEFE01D189C" pageId="18" pageNumber="131">
As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="A452D06FCDC814712072FCC1083D59CC" author="Toledano, L" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs on Biodiversity" pageId="27" pageNumber="140" pagination="81 - 130" title="Systematic notes on the Bembidiina of the northern Andes with particular reference to the fauna of Ecuador (Coleoptera, Carabidae)." volume="1" year="2008">Toledano (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<normalizedToken id="71418E268292249D4463365185C490FC" originalValue="Jeannelâ€™s">Jeannel's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName id="6991E89C0EF8CFBDD3A601E91B7FA49D" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphus</taxonomicName>
was polyphyletic, with at least 
<taxonomicName id="F59F24493177CB446F992510B9883252" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion hirtipes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirtipes">Bembidion hirtipes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CE94044A2A2B25BFD95DBCA0BCDC583F" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion ringueleti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ringueleti">Bembidion ringueleti</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="81CA4D39D14A871C4C8021FC6B7C8899" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion rufoplagiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoplagiatum">Bembidion rufoplagiatum</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="40DE6FB42D0DD9FE59C6730D44F06FE0" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion uniforme" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uniforme">Bembidion uniforme</taxonomicName>
Csiki belonging within 
<taxonomicName id="FF61C270145CA04C49150C1DB2D17BD8" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
. This is confirmed in part by my results (Fig. 8, Table 3). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="A644AB240E67CFD7139B770B20BB591B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion engelhardti" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="engelhardti">Bembidion engelhardti</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="31F51347943E64166B24CCD540BC343D" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion eburneonigrum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburneonigrum">Bembidion eburneonigrum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D029C59E195111F483A0C66E8130CB81" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion tucumanum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tucumanum">Bembidion tucumanum</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="526991A37FE9CAAE93E6F9EEF9169E29" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion germainianum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="germainianum">Bembidion germainianum</taxonomicName>
are members of 
<taxonomicName id="8A4351BBDE9AFACC42A5011A4FDAC652" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Nothonepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothonepha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothonepha</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName id="643B3148BBA0B22A74898632658B4A6B" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphus</taxonomicName>
. Of the species included in the subgenus by 
<bibRefCitation id="D669CF842337221730977424C08EF33A" author="Jeannel, R" editor="Deboutteville, CD" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="26" pageNumber="139" pagination="527 - 655" title="Les Trechides de la Paleantarctide occidentale." volumeTitle="Biologie de l'Amerique Australe, Etudes sur la Faune du Sol" year="1962">Jeannel (1962)</bibRefCitation>
, this leaves only the type species, 
<taxonomicName id="F7CD1C383DE11E858FB9C70405BFF37A" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium philippii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippii">Bembidium philippii</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 2A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5590B474BA88F4EEC85B9E5000CEE09" pageId="18" pageNumber="131">
In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="D9AE7C072949FE91C82C4EFBFC7C27AD" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion peterseni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peterseni">Bembidion peterseni</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="DC89F177C462B11F19AD6F197FB0F16C" author="Jensen-Haarup, AC" journalOrPublisher="Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="26" pageNumber="139" pagination="541 - 554" title="New species of Coleoptera from West Argentina." volume="1910" year="1910">Jensen-Haarup (1910)</bibRefCitation>
, from Mendoza, Argentina, can tentatively be placed here. I have examined a male syntype (in ZMUC), and it is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="2EE9F83D2383F5F8FC2B1D7D99D89877" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium philippii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippii">Bembidium philippii</taxonomicName>
, although with much deeper and longer elytral striae. It is not a member of 
<taxonomicName id="38E85784E73F99EAF1857CF65E1868AB" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Nothonepha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nothonepha" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothonepha</taxonomicName>
(as it lacks mesepisternal pits), nor is it a member of 
<taxonomicName id="7E4769A7692DAC322E1AA35942648EA1" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
(it has a brush sclerite, and does not have the long flagellum characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="1EAF39B3DDDE013EA2C578496CCFE65D" authority="Jeannel, 1962" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Antiperyphanes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antiperyphanes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Antiperyphanes</taxonomicName>
). The internal sac of the male genitalia, although difficult to see because of the nature of the preparation, appears very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="26A242BA1EC7207EBA071C5C33510382" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidium philippii" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippii">Bembidium philippii</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4627EDFB01198A4BFD6F958A52F80028" pageId="18" pageNumber="131">
B. philippii is common on sand shores of rivers in the provinces of 
<normalizedToken id="A13DC037EB48536F57208FC4A5B43289" originalValue="NeuquÃ©n">Neuquen</normalizedToken>
and Chubut in Argentina; it also occurs in Chile.
</paragraph>
